<h1 class="mb-4">Theme Customization</h1>

<div class="card mb-4">
  <div class="card-header">Theming System</div>
  <p>Larify includes a flexible theming system that allows you to easily switch between light and dark modes and customize your application's appearance.</p>
  
  <h3>CSS Variables</h3>
  <p>The framework uses CSS variables to manage colors and styles:</p>
  <pre><code>:root {
  --primary-color: #4a6cf7;
  --secondary-color: #6b7280;
  --background-color: #ffffff;
  --text-color: #1f2937;
  --card-background: #f9fafb;
  --border-color: #e5e7eb;
  --header-background: #f3f4f6;
  --success-color: #10b981;
  --error-color: #ef4444;
  --warning-color: #f59e0b;
}</code></pre>
</div>

<div class="card mb-4">
  <div class="card-header">Implementing Dark Mode</div>
  
  <p>To implement dark mode in your application, you can add the following JavaScript to your layout:</p>
  
  <h4>Add Theme Toggle to Layout</h4>
  <pre><code>&lt;button id="theme-toggle" class="btn btn-sm">
  &lt;i class="icon-moon">&lt;/i> Toggle Theme
&lt;/button>

&lt;script>
  const themeToggle = document.getElementById('theme-toggle');
  const prefersDark = window.matchMedia('(prefers-color-scheme: dark)');
  
  // Initialize theme from local storage or system preference
  function initTheme() {
    const savedTheme = localStorage.getItem('theme');
    if (savedTheme === 'dark' || (!savedTheme && prefersDark.matches)) {
      document.documentElement.classList.add('dark-theme');
    }
  }
  
  // Toggle theme
  themeToggle.addEventListener('click', () => {
    document.documentElement.classList.toggle('dark-theme');
    const isDark = document.documentElement.classList.contains('dark-theme');
    localStorage.setItem('theme', isDark ? 'dark' : 'light');
  });
  
  // Initialize on page load
  initTheme();
&lt;/script></code></pre>
</div>

<div class="card mb-4">
  <div class="card-header">Dark Theme CSS Variables</div>
  
  <p>Add these CSS rules to implement dark mode:</p>
  
  <pre><code>.dark-theme {
  --primary-color: #6d8bfa;
  --secondary-color: #9ca3af;
  --background-color: #111827;
  --text-color: #f9fafb;
  --card-background: #1f2937;
  --border-color: #374151;
  --header-background: #1f2937;
  --success-color: #34d399;
  --error-color: #f87171;
  --warning-color: #fbbf24;
}</code></pre>
</div>

<div class="card">
  <div class="card-header">Component Theming</div>
  <p>All components in Larify automatically adapt to theme changes. To theme a custom component, use the CSS variables:</p>
  
  <pre><code>.custom-component {
  background-color: var(--card-background);
  color: var(--text-color);
  border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
}</code></pre>
  
